description:
When multiple method overloads exist with different parameter types, the VM should select the most specific overload using is_subtype_expr(). Example:

  void process(Animal a) { ... }
  void process(Dog d) { ... }
  Dog fido = new Dog();
  process(fido); // should pick process(Dog), not process(Animal)

Currently the VM resolves methods by name only (no overload resolution). This is the lowest-priority consumer — most programs work without it, and few Rosetta/Exercism tests exercise overloading.
